<h1>Reproduce every number yourself</h1>

<p>All outputs in this repository are generated by scripts from FOAA-obtained raw data. Running a single command from a clean clone reproduces everything.</p>

<h2>Prerequisites</h2>

<ul>
  <li>Python 3.11+</li>
  <li><a href="https://docs.astral.sh/uv/">uv</a> (Python package manager)</li>
  <li>git</li>
</ul>

<h2>Steps</h2>

<pre><code>git clone https://github.com/cristoslc/data-for-press-release-2026-05-08.git
cd data-for-press-release-2026-05-08
./run.sh</code></pre>

<h2>What <code>run.sh</code> does</h2>

<ol class="methodology-steps">
  <li>Deduplicate raw audit logs → <code>outputs/audit-logs-deduplicated/</code></li>
  <li>Normalize shared-network org names → <code>data/derived/sppd-shared-networks/</code></li>
  <li>Classify assist-other-agency searches → <code>outputs/assist-other-agencies/</code></li>
  <li>Cross-index SPPD network against ICE 287(g) → <code>outputs/sppd-287g-crossindex/</code></li>
  <li>Count unique states → <code>outputs/sppd-sharing-states/</code></li>
</ol>

<h2>Verifying data integrity</h2>

<p>Every input file has a SHA-256 hash recorded in its METHODOLOGY.md. You can verify that your clone hasn't been tampered with:</p>

<pre><code>shasum -a 256 data/sppd-foaa-2026-audit-logs/raw-monthly/SharedNetworks_2026_May_5.csv
# Expected: 75729defe7be5ad5454423b815fba159bb456675813dec41fa1e7342f440c19c</code></pre>

<h2>Data provenance</h2>

<p>All raw data was obtained via FOAA (Freedom of Access Act) requests filed directly by No Flock for SoPo to the South Portland Police Department. The unmodified originals are in <a href="{{ "/data/sppd-foaa-2026-audit-logs/raw-monthly/" | url }}">data/sppd-foaa-2026-audit-logs/raw-monthly/</a>. Outputs in <a href="{{ "/outputs/" | url }}">outputs/</a> are derived from those originals through the scripts in <a href="{{ "/analysis/" | url }}">analysis/</a>.</p>